ρ = 2 *(1+ cosϕ)
w=\sqrt{z}
u^2 + v^2=2u
z=x+ iy
w=u+iy
z(\varphi) = 2(1+\cos\varphi)e^{i\varphi}
z = x+iy = w^2 = (u+iv)=^2 = u^2-v^2 + i2uv
\begin{align} u^2 - v^2 &= 2(1+\cos \varphi)\cos\varphi & 2uv &= 2(1+\cos\varphi)\sin\varphi\\ \leadsto u^2-v^2 &= 4\cos^2 \frac{\varphi}{2}\left(\cos^2 \frac{\varphi}{2} - \sin^2 \frac{\varphi}{2}\right) & 2uv &= 4\cos^2 \frac{\varphi}{2}\left(2\sin\frac{\varphi}{2}\cos\frac{\varphi}{2}\right) \end{align}
\begin{align}u &= 2\cos^2 \frac{\varphi}{2} & v &= 2\sin\frac{\varphi}{2}\cos\frac{\varphi}{2}\\ \leadsto u &= 1 + \cos\varphi & v &= \sin \varphi. \end{align}
u^2 + v^2 = (1+\cos\varphi)^2 + \sin^2\varphi = 1 + 2\cos\varphi + \cos^2\varphi + \sin^2\varphi = 2(1+\cos\varphi) = 2u.
